  "http://www.radlex.org/RID/Definition" : [ {
    "@value" : "Codes that identify the kind of stage reported in an Observation, necessary to correctly interpret the value associated with a staging Observation. In terms of the SNOMED CT hierarchy, these codes represent observable entities. If the staging system used to determine the stage is not implicit in this code, the staging system must be separately recorded in Observation.method. More specific staging profiles, if available, should be consulted before determining the correct code."
  } ],
